  "body": "Similar to https://github.com/MyCryptoHQ/MyCrypto/issues/1960, https://github.com/MyCryptoHQ/MyCrypto/pull/1971\r\n\r\nAll TREZOR and Ledger devices with passphrases are not able to unlock on Desktop. Recently, support for entering a PIN was added via https://github.com/MyCryptoHQ/MyCrypto/pull/1971. The same framework can be used for entering your passphrase. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n![screen shot 2018-07-10 at 1 43 33 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7861465/42530613-457272c0-8447-11e8-9c82-20f948d65270.png)\r\n\r\nAs reference, I've added a screenshot showing how TREZOR behaves in a web context, where they have permissions to a window: \r\n![screen shot 2018-07-10 at 1 33 28 pm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7861465/42530755-98ceeade-8447-11e8-9d10-ae147b9f0580.png)\r\n\r\n- [ ] Pop window open so users can enter passphrases on Ledger and TREZOR when a passphrase is set on the device. ",
